<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="609" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="609">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="609">
<bibRefCitation author="Wood, SL" journalOrPublisher="Brigham Young University, M. L. Bean Life Science Museum; Provo" pageId="0" pageNumber="609" refId="B91" refString="Wood, SL, 2007. Bark and ambrosia beetles of South America (Coleoptera: Scolytidae). Brigham Young University, M.L. Bean Life Science Museum; Provo" title="Bark and ambrosia beetles of South America (Coleoptera: Scolytidae)." year="2007">Wood (2007)</bibRefCitation>
reports this species as introduced into Africa but published reports were not located. This erroneous record appears to be due to a reference to the species in the description of the African species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eggers" authorityYear="1932" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xyleborus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xyleborus ovatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="609" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ovatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="609">Xyleborus ovatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Eggers, H" journalOrPublisher="Revue de Zoologie et de Botanique Africaines" pageId="0" pageNumber="609" pagination="191 - 304" refId="B28" refString="Eggers, H, 1932. Neue Borkenkafer (Ipidae, Col.) aus Africa (Nachtrag V.). Revue de Zoologie et de Botanique Africaines 22: 191 - 304" title="Neue Borkenkafer (Ipidae, Col.) aus Africa (Nachtrag V.)." volume="22" year="1932">Eggers (1932</bibRefCitation>
: 298) in which Eggers compared the form of 
<taxonomicName family="Curculionidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. ovatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="609" rank="species" species="ovatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="609">X. ovatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to that of the South American species 
<taxonomicName family="Curculionidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. coartatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="609" rank="species" species="coartatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="609">X. coartatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but did not state that the latter species occurred in Africa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
